Back to Top

Educational Attainment data is complied using Table B15002 from the 2015 ACS 5-Year estimates. Nationally, about 13.53% of Americans have less than a High School diploma and about 24.39% have a Bachelor’s Degree or higher.

Limited English Proficiency

Back to Top

Limited English Proficiency (LEP) refers to the proportion of individuals who speak a language other than english at home & speak english less than “very well”. Limited English Proficiency data is complied using Table B16004 from the 2015 ACS 5-Year estimates. Nationally Among Americans who speak a language other than english at home, about 33.8% of them speak English less than “very well”.
